KANO – Director General Ahmed Tinubu Support Group, Abdulmumuni Jibrin Kofa on Friday exited from the ruling All Progressives Congress over irreconcilable differences with party leadership in Kano. The controversial former Chairman, House Committee on Appropriations was sighted on Friday afternoon in company of members of the New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP). In a picture that was circulated to Reporters in Kano on Friday, Jibrin Kofa was seen lifting a basket, the insignia of the party. -Advertisement- As at time of going to press, Mr. Kofa could not be reached. Details soon…